Basic syntax:

```r
function_name <- function(arg1, arg2, ...) {
  # code that does something
  return(result)
}
```

You assign the function to a name, then call it like `function_name(value1, value2)`.

slides.codeSnippet:
add <- function(x, y) {
  result <- x + y
  return(result)
}

# Call it
add(3, 5)
add(10, -2)
